<title type="html"><![CDATA[Konami VRC4/6/7 IRQs in PAL system?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5152&amp;p=46875#p46875"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">16 sprites per line<br /></div><br />That would be awesome on the NES.</div><br />Indeed it would. While not possible with an unmodified console, it would be possible to hack in a second "slave" PPU which would allow for that. Nintendo's PPU-related patents mention that. However, on the NES board the four PPU EXT pins are all grounded, so you'd have to do some reworking. Plus write your own software to take advantage of the feature. <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br /><br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />That wasn't so clear during the NES's commercial era. The Super Famicom/NES was originally slated to have NES back-compat.<br /></div><br />Yes, the SNES PPU1 and PPU2 chips have pins mysteriously called HVCMODE. I always wondered what someone who is handy with a logic analyser could figure out about that feature...<br /><br /><br />-- M<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=316">mark_k</a> — Sat May 16, 2009 10:12 am</p><hr />
