<author><name><![CDATA[MottZilla]]></name></author>
<updated>2009-05-08T12:04:22-07:00</updated>
<published>2009-05-08T12:04:22-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5152&amp;p=46659#p46659</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5152&amp;p=46659#p46659"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Konami VRC4/6/7 IRQs in PAL system?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5152&amp;p=46659#p46659"><![CDATA[
Konami VRC4 and up count CPU cycles they do not use the PPU at all. You can clearly observe this behavior by the way the games set the IRQ target number at NMI if I recall as that is the frame of reference point you have to set it at. Also it's known that the counter counts even if rendering is off or not happening.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1726">MottZilla</a> — Fri May 08, 2009 12:04 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
